  "standardBio": "Celestora, titled among keepers as “Sunlane Guide,” carries hopeful duty in every movement. Native to Celestial Rift, the species clarifies through sunshaft and pale gold, leaving traces that other Riftlings can follow like soft maps. Wild groups form loose bonds rather than rigid packs; a calm individual may become the emotional center of a small hearthline. They eat Radiant Lily eagerly and dislike food that smells of neglect or spoilage. Ancient keepers carved Celestora silhouettes into travel stones, believing the species guided the lost. Modern hatcheries record them as reliable companions; their social intelligence tuned to group moods makes training feel like conversation. Their signature ability, Star Silk, reflects a life shaped by Celestial Rift more than by arena ambition. Their quiet is mistaken for emptiness. In truth they are listening harder than louder species. Young Celestoras practice Star Silk as play long before they understand battle. Adults teach by demonstration: where to rest, what to avoid, how to share warmth or shade.",
